      "writtenOn": "2020-01-21T19:26:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why do we want to constraint the note? A user might like to e.g. annotate an ignore with a stack trace, a list with bullet points, etc.\n\nIf it\u0027s a UI thing then we should address it in the UI, e.g. with a \"show more\" link that expands the note beyond its first line.\n\nIf we really must have a limit, then consider making it a few orders of magnitude larger. For reference, 1kb is roughly 13 80-character lines.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 824,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 831,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "03acd2e5f7ed053641e925abc4f61e160b85d39a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3d5dd5bd_9b5c9f34",
        "filename": "golden/go/web/web.go",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 831,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-22T15:13:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If there\u0027s a lot of context/stacktrace, etc, I want that to happen in a linked bug, which is by and away the most common usage. \n\nI\u0027ve never actually seen very long notes; this change was purely defensive so that we have \"some\" limit.\n\nActing on your advice though, I checked through the prod data to look for filter length. The longest was 1.1 KB, so I increased the limit to 10kb for filters.",
      "parentUuid": "1d89eb77_eaaa9502",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 824,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 831,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "03acd2e5f7ed053641e925abc4f61e160b85d39a",
